Text.SourceString: Well, well, well… If it isn’t the new owner of <Italic>the lot</>.//Or should I say, “the farm”?
Sure, the farm.//Apologies, I haven’t introduced myself. My name is <NPCName>Walter</>.
We’re fortunate that we’re able to grow grapes all year round. Of course, that doesn’t come cheap.
But it shows quality, I hope. Our greenhouse is built from the best materials.//Withstands the strongest wind.
It’s okay to indulge in treats occasionally, but doing it time and again can affect your health.
That’s what <NPCName>Yuri</> said when I told her about my…errr…bad habit.//<portrait=normal>Be well, my friend.
We’re fortunate that we’re able to grow grapes all year round. Of course, that doesn’t come cheap.
But it shows quality, I hope. Our greenhouse is built from the best materials.//Withstands the strongest wind.
I’m proud to say the wine and sake served at the Tavern are ours.//They’re local and very high quality.
I like to deliver our products to the inn and the Tavern personally.//<portrait=normal>Gives me a reason to visit the town.
I’m proud to say the wine and sake served at the Tavern are ours.//They’re local and very high quality.
I like to deliver our products to the inn and the Tavern personally.//<portrait=normal>Gives me a reason to visit the town.
There must be many hidden treasures on this island. We found our own lost heirloom some time ago.//<portrait=normal>I’m sure it wasn’t the only one out there.
It’s okay to indulge in treats occasionally, but doing it time and again can affect your health.
That’s what <NPCName>Yuri</> said when I told her about my…errr…bad habit.//<portrait=normal>Be well, my friend.
Technology, huh? Automatic sprinklers and such.//<portrait=normal>What a time to be a farmer!
There must be many hidden treasures on this island. We found our own lost heirloom some time ago.//<portrait=normal>I’m sure it wasn’t the only one out there.
I like to spend my weekends at the vineyard. Invite some friends over… You know?
Here for a visit, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Technology, huh? Automatic sprinklers and such.//<portrait=normal>What a time to be a farmer!
The islanders here are very friendly. That’s how they get you to stay.
Well, I sure don’t mind the warm hospitality.//Quite like it, in fact.
There’s a lot of labor involved in the farm business, even if the farm is automated.//For one, you still need to make sure the crop quality is acceptable.
There’s a lot of quality control work in this type of industry… Food and beverages, that is.//<portrait=normal>Because if one batch is bad, you run the risk of losing clients.
There’s a lot of labor involved in the farm business, even if the farm is automated.//For one, you still need to make sure the crop quality is acceptable.
Let me give you some free advice… There’s a lot of quality control work in this type of industry. Food and beverages, that is.
You see, because if one batch is bad, you run the risk of losing clients… Once you lose them, they may never come back.
I can give you some insight on the Tavern boys. I know them quite well, in fact. <NPCName>Noah</> and <NPCName>Frank</> are brothers.
One more thing about the Tavern boys… One of them likes durian, and the other hates it.//Can’t remember which is which, though.//So, good luck figuring that one out.
Carrots and grapes can be used in so many ways.//Snacking, for one… Well, I personally like carrots as snacks, but grapes not so much.
The islanders here are very friendly. That’s how they get you to stay.
Well, I sure don’t mind the warm hospitality.//Quite like it, in fact.

One more thing about the Tavern boys… One of them likes durian, and the other hates it.//Can’t remember which is which, though.//So, good luck figuring that one out.
There’s a lot of quality control work in this type of industry… Food and beverages, that is.//<portrait=normal>Because if one batch is bad, you run the risk of losing clients.
There’s a lot of labor involved in the farm business, even if the farm is automated.//For one, you still need to make sure the crop quality is acceptable.
Carrots and grapes can be used in so many ways.//Snacking, for one… Well, I personally like carrots as snacks, but grapes not so much.
Diamonds are just rocks… Shiny, yes, but they’re rocks, for heaven’s sake.//<portrait=normal>I don’t get the appeal.
Well… I can assure you I wouldn’t object if, let’s say, I were given a diamond.//<portrait=normal>It would be valuable, regardless.
Ah… I’m ready to take my evening break.
How’s your Tuesday been so far, <PlayerName>$player</>?
For farmers like us, having a set harvest schedule is important… A seasonal goal of some sort.
Oh well. I guess to each their own.
I don’t play any musical instruments well at all… But I can play.//I’d hope so, since I took several semesters of music back in my university years.

I’m what they call a natural talent at golf. I don’t mean to brag, but I have to admit it. Keeping secrets just doesn’t sit right with me.//<portrait=happy>I’m very good at golf… Ah. Relieved now it’s out in the open.
For farmers like us, having a set harvest schedule is important… A seasonal goal of some sort.
Oh well. I guess to each their own.
I like to go to town in the evening to see the shenanigans myself.
I only do that on weekdays. On weekends, the town’s too hectic for my taste.
I don’t know if you can call Friday the weekend yet, since the week hasn’t ended for some people.
A discussion for another day, perhaps.
Diamonds are just rocks… Shiny, yes, but they’re rocks, for heaven’s sake.//<portrait=normal>I don’t get the appeal.
Well… I can assure you I wouldn’t object if, let’s say, I were given a diamond.//<portrait=normal>It would be valuable, regardless.
I’m reserving my weekend for dancing.//Isn’t that what folks do?
Oh yes, I am… You haven’t seen anything yet.//<portrait=normal>Catch me dancing one of these nights, and you shall see some poetry in motion.
What a week, huh?
It’s been a while since I last played the banjo. I think I might start the week by picking it back up.
Oh, banjo playing is quite the art. We should, shall I say, “jam”?//<portrait=normal>Ah yes… We should jam sometime.
I don’t play any musical instruments well at all… But I can play.//I’d hope so, since I took several semesters of music back in my university years.

I’m what they call a natural talent at golf. I don’t mean to brag, but I have to admit it. Keeping secrets just doesn’t sit right with me.//<portrait=happy>I’m very good at golf… Ah. Relieved now it’s out in the open.
Oh, I’ve heard of Pufferfish! I don’t have anything to do with the deal they’re making.
I found out the same time as everyone else.
As your lawyer and a fellow farmer, I advise you to diversify your crops each season.
You’re right. I’m not your lawyer. The pollen is making my brain funny.
My wife loves any kind of jam. The first time she learned how to make it, she made everything into jam.
Pineapple? Jam. Grape? Jam. Banana? Jam!//We had to share it with the whole island so <NPCName>Luke</> and I wouldn’t have to eat jam for every meal.
More people should garden. As my wife puts it, it’s calming, and it’s an excellent mental exercise.
It teaches patience. I can confirm that.//<portrait=happy>I’m a much more calm, peaceful, happy, and calm person now than I was before.
Did I say “calm” twice? Easy mistake.//<portrait=annoyed>If only it weren’t so hot in here. Argh… Never mind.
More people should garden. As my wife puts it, it’s calming, and it’s an excellent mental exercise.
It teaches patience. I can confirm that.//<portrait=happy>I’m a much more calm, peaceful, happy, and calm person now than I was before.
Did I say “calm” twice? Easy mistake.//<portrait=annoyed>If only it weren’t so hot in here. Argh… Never mind.
There are coconuts on the beach this time of year.
They make a nice drink on hot Summer days.
Do you feel a bit, um…
Sticky lately? I blame the heat.
Holding a dance in heat like this wouldn’t be my first instinct.
Yet the good mayor keeps doing it. Given the amount we pay in taxes, I think we should have a say about things like this. Don’t you think?
The heat isn’t agreeing with my brain… I feel fuzzy.
I should lie down with a big glass of orange juice.
Well, well, well. The Harvest Festival is right around the corner. I’m intrigued to see what you have up your sleeve, Farmer <PlayerName>$player</>.
<NPCName>Luke</> is protective of Taco.//It would break his heart if Taco ever… You know.
*sighs*
We purchased the vineyard and the house together. But of course, it didn’t look like it does now.
It was much smaller back then. We added some rooms, did this and that. Looks much better now, I think.
The snow is bad news for us. The crops are dying, and production is down more than 50 percent.
During Winter, I’m sure you’re not swimming in money either. But there are other means to get more income, if you’re into that sort of thing. Like fishing or mining.
If you haven’t already, it may be the best time to try to upgrade your farming tools.
That reminds me. I have to see the mayor next week. I always offer him a free tax consultation. It’s the least I can do for the town.
Aside from our monetary donation to the island, of course… But who’s counting, right?
The Sanchez brothers take a bit long to upgrade tools. I wish they’d install some new machines to speed things up.//A couple of days here and there with no tools really reduces efficiency.
Do you want me to speak with them, <PlayerName>$player</>? Perhaps I can get you a bit of a discount to compensate for your lost revenue.
<NPCName>Luke</> is protective of Taco.//It would break his heart if Taco ever… You know.
*sighs*
That reminds me; I have to see the mayor next week… I always offer him a free consultation about taxes.//It’s the least I can do for the town.
Aside from our monetary donation to the island, of course… But who’s counting, right?
My wife loves any kind of jam. The first time she learned how to make it, she made everything into jam.
Pineapple? Jam. Grape? Jam. Banana? Jam!//We had to share it with the whole island so <NPCName>Luke</> and I wouldn’t have to eat jam for every meal.
Excuse me.
The rain makes things much easier for us farmers, huh?
It’s probably good weather to mine for ore.
Ah, what do I know? I don’t even do that. Ha ha.
Are you on your way to town? If you see him, will you please tell <NPCName>Sam</> I won’t have any wine to sell today?
What would one do on a lazy night like this?
I should read a book. It seems like the perfect time to read a book.
I’m a little worried about the crops. I hope the storm doesn’t destroy them.
Check your fences tomorrow, because sometimes a storm this big can cause damage.
I’ll most certainly check on ours. The last one broke a couple of fences and destroyed some crops.
That reminds me. I have to see the mayor next week. I always offer him a free tax consultation. It’s the least I can do for the town.
Aside from our monetary donation to the island, of course… But who’s counting, right?
We’re literally in the middle of a storm, <PlayerName>$player</>. Doesn’t it bother you?
We’re literally in the middle of a storm, <PlayerName>$player</>. Doesn’t it bother you?
It’s probably good weather to mine for ore.
Ah, what do I know? I don’t even do that. Ha ha.
To keep our house warm, we need four times the energy it takes to heat a regular house.
Now, if that’s not a waste, I don’t know what is.
To keep our house warm, we need four times the energy it takes to heat a regular house.
Now, if that’s not a waste, I don’t know what is.
If it’s nothing urgent, I really should get going, <PlayerName>$player</>. Not the best place to chitchat.
Ah, our farmer neighbor! To what do I owe the pleasure?
The view from here is unbeatable. It’s the main reason we purchased the place.
It’s not hard to grow grapes. They basically grow themselves.
This is our best crop to date.
Well, can you blame a guy for being proud of his crops if they’re this good? Nah! You can’t.
You’re a friend of my son, <NPCName>Luke</>, right? I’ve seen you two in town several times.
I’m glad he’s making new friends.
We don’t sell individual bottles here. But if you want to try our wine, the Tavern carries it.
We mostly sell our wine abroad… To restaurants and hotels.//Boutique hotels, mostly. Very exclusive.
Ah, what can I say? It’s who we are.//Exclusivity is part of our brand.
We supply the inn with several cases a season.//Guests enjoy our local grapes, and we’re part of Coral Island’s identity.
We supply the Tavern with several cases a season.//Guests enjoy our local grapes, and we’re part of Coral Island’s identity.
It’s probably not the best idea to have too many of these.
Maybe I’ll dance a bit after this to burn these off.
Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>! Fancy a drink tonight?//You look like you could use one.
Or three. Heh heh heh.
<NPCName>Bree</> cooks almost all our meals… Why, of course, I help. Not a lot. I do help a bit.//In the grand scheme of things.
I help with the dishes. The cooking is all hers.//I give you that… Why are you bringing this up, anyway?
The Sanchez brothers take a bit long to upgrade tools. I wish they’d install some new machines to speed things up.//A couple of days here and there with no tools really reduces efficiency.
Do you want me to speak with them, <PlayerName>$player</>? Perhaps I can get you a bit of a discount to compensate for your lost revenue.
Looking for <NPCName>Bree</>? No, she didn’t come with me.//I believe she’s taking a solitary hike to clear her mind.
I’m not sure where she is exactly, but she loves the beach. If you’re looking for her, try the lookout.
This house is too big for the four of us.
I’m definitely paying too much tax on this house.//I wish we had ghosts here. That way, at least the expense wouldn’t be wasted on just us four.
This house is too big for the four of us.
We’re paying too much tax and wasting too much heat to keep all that empty space warm.
<NPCName>Bree</> cooks almost all our meals… But I do help a bit in the grand scheme of things.
I help with the dishes. The cooking is all hers.
It’s an interesting choice for a young person like yourself to suddenly take up farming.//<portrait=normal>Now, I hope that didn’t come out as prying.
I must admit, at first I didn’t think you’d succeed, but now I have nothing but praise.
*yawns*
It’s hard to focus on anything here. This house is too relaxing.//<portrait=happy>It’s a good thing, I hope… Because this house is anything but cheap. Ha ha!
When <NPCName>Bree</> and I first started the vineyard… Ah, I didn’t expect much out of it.//Just a little hobby to keep <NPCName>Bree</> busy. But now…
I hope you agree with me on this. I believe our beverages have become a part of Coral Island’s identity.//<portrait=normal>The wine, especially, is its signature drink.
When <NPCName>Bree</> and I first started the vineyard… Ah, I didn’t expect much out of it.//Just a little hobby to keep <NPCName>Bree</> busy. But now…
I hope you agree with me on this. I believe our beverages have become a part of Coral Island’s identity.//<portrait=normal>The wine, especially, is its signature drink.

People often generalize without realizing it.//For one thing, we grow grapes, and so people assume we produce wine. What if, let’s just say, I grew grapes for fun because I love grapes, and I want to feed wildlife?
That’s why people shouldn’t assume. But yes, I do indeed produce wine, and no, I don’t intend to feed grapes to wildlife.//<portrait=annoyed>What’s your point?
In my life, I’ve met a lot of different kinds of people, <PlayerName>$player</>. Let me just give you another piece of free advice… Don’t judge too quickly.//Sometimes what we see isn’t what we get.
And it goes both ways. Wolves can look like sheep, true. But sheep can sometimes look like wolves too.//<portrait=normal>I should start charging you for all this advice – what do you say? Ha ha!
We have a couple of properties downtown. Well, the electronics store is one of them… Ah, here’s a fun anecdote.//We almost bought the Pufferfish building.
We also made an offer on that beautiful villa at the beach.//It was an old friend’s… They declined. Ah, too bad.//<portrait=normal>Would’ve made a good vacation home.
Our dog likes to sneak out of the house and wander into town by himself.//Sometimes he comes back with mud on his paws. Drives <NPCName>Bree</> mad! But I can never get too upset at him.
I don’t worry much about Taco. The townies seem to like him.//<portrait=normal>And walking around is good exercise for him.
You’re a hard worker, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Just like my son, <NPCName>Luke</>.
It’s a lot for one person to run a farm like yours.//I’ll have to visit one of these days, just to scope out my competition. Heh heh!
Do you know I didn’t go to school to learn wine making? Self-taught.//With all the competitions we’ve won, it must look like we’re experts… Ah, I hope I don’t sound arrogant.
Well, maybe a <Italic>little</> arrogance isn’t a bad thing.//I mean, we’ve both come this far in life. Must take pride, do you agree?

I studied law in my youth and practiced it for years. But a life of confrontation can be tiring after a while.//I prefer peace and quiet, such as this…//I can’t give you any specific, tailored legal advice, of course, but I’m happy to provide general information if you have any legal questions.//I do that for free nowadays.

I don’t practice law anymore.//<portrait=normal>Well… I do, actually, only part time. I don’t actively advertise.//Besides, it’s nearly impossible to find clients around here, so, why bother to advertise, right?
Although I still represent one or two clients from overseas… Well, somebody has to have a real job in this house, right?//<portrait=annoyed>Not everyone can play farmer all day or sell toys.
One could say that my wife and I met at a work event, sure.//<portrait=normal>She isn’t a lawyer, so we didn’t meet at <Italic>my</> work event.
It was her work event. Beautiful-looking lady. What can a man do but fall in love, don’t you agree?//Love at first sight. What can I say? Ha!
<NPCName>Bree</> never did get along with my friends back in the city…not with them, not with their wives.//I don’t blame her.
My friends can be dismissive toward outsiders.//What can I do? I like them. Don’t mix them up, and things will be just fine. I hope.
I have some properties abroad, not just here on Coral Island. They’re good investments.//<portrait=happy>And if we visit Pokyo or Dulca, we don’t have to worry about where to stay.

That green-haired doctor is the smart one, don’t you agree? She accurately diagnosed my stomach problem, and it hasn’t hurt since.//Now, I had that problem for a long time… Ah, forgot what it was. A fine doctor, that one.

The pain came and went. I never paid much attention to it since it didn’t hurt that much… But she fixed it right up.//<portrait=happy>I have to recommend her to my friends in the city. She’s a smart doctor. My son’s friend, I think…
I’m no good at running… I prefer fast walking or a nice game of golf.//<portrait=normal>Less demanding.
It’s not that I’m not capable of running, of course.//I can run very fast… Just don’t like it, that’s all.
I heard rumors that monsters live in the cavern behind there. Is that true?
Nobody mentioned it to me before we moved in. If it were true, I’d sue the town!//I wouldn’t feel safe living here.

You can try planting some grapes now, I hope. But careful, they wither come Winter… The ones you get from Sam’s, anyway.//The grapes in our vineyard are special. They grow all year long for some reason, not just in Fall.
We don’t participate in the Harvest Festival… We don’t have enough crops for it.//You will, won’t you?
What are you wearing, Farmer? Don’t cheap out on clothes during Winter.//<portrait=normal>Wear only top-of-the-line wool. It’s worth it.
Our dog, Taco, doesn’t seem to mind the cold.//We have all kinds of dog sweaters, but no… That neckerchief is the only thing he wants to wear.
Summer doesn’t seem to deter Taco from exploring around.//<portrait=concerned>I hope he gets enough water throughout the day. I don’t want him to get heatstroke…

Heatstroke is no joke, Farmer.//<portrait=normal>A friend of mine, nice fella… We were just sitting at the beach, enjoying a Sunday, and it came out of nowhere.//<portrait=happy>He had to move to a shadier place. Ha ha! Looking back, it was a little funny.
